.TH "sg_copy_buffer" 9 "sg_copy_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sg_copy_buffer \- Copy data between a linear buffer and an SG list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "size_t" sg_copy_buffer
.BI "(struct scatterlist *sgl "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nents "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t buflen "  ","
.BI "off_t skip "  ","
.BI "bool to_buffer "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sgl" 12
The SG list
.IP "nents" 12
Number of SG entries
.IP "buf" 12
Where to copy from
.IP "buflen" 12
The number of bytes to copy
.IP "skip" 12
Number of bytes to skip before copying
.IP "to_buffer" 12
transfer direction (true == from an sg list to a
buffer, false == from a buffer to an sg list)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of copied bytes.
